ProtoDefines:
. "A transformation $\mathbf{L}: \R^n \to \R^m$ defined on all
   of $\R^n$ is {\it linear } if $$ 
   \mathbf{L}(\mathbf{X}+\mathbf{Y})=\mathbf{L}(\mathbf{X})+\mathbf{L}(\mathbf{Y})
   $$ for all $\mathbf{X}$ and $\mathbf{Y}$ in $\R^n$ and $$ 
   \mathbf{L}(a\mathbf{X})=a\mathbf{L}(\mathbf{X}) $$ for all 
   $\mathbf{X}$ in $\R^n$ and real numbers $a$."
